CatDescriptText: Mrs. Mary Plump, 3208 Dawson Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 26, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "In your opinion, what constitutes the 'Leadership' in Negro community in Pittsburgh? What do you think of that which exists?" answer reads: "I think that it's pretty good."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mary Plump wearing coat with four buttons, holding light colored clutch handbag, standing in front of Rosenbaum Company with fur store, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
